trans-unit.source: Provides the base implementation for all controls that contain single content and have a header.
trans-unit.target: Fornece a implementação base para todos os controles que contêm conteúdo único e têm um cabeçalho.

trans-unit.source: HeaderedContentControl inherits the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> property from <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl> and defines the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> property that is of type <xref:System.Object>.
trans-unit.target: HeaderedContentControl herda a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>propriedade de <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl>e define a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A>propriedade que é do tipo <xref:System.Object>.</xref:System.Object> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> provides a heading for the control.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A>Fornece um título para o controle.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A>

trans-unit.source: Like the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> property of a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl>, the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> can be any type.
trans-unit.target: Como o <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>propriedade de um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl>, o <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A>pode ser qualquer tipo.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>

trans-unit.source: The following illustration shows two <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem> objects, which inherit from HeaderedContentControl.
trans-unit.target: A ilustração a seguir mostra duas <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem>objetos, que herdam de HeaderedContentControl.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem>

trans-unit.source: The first <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem> has <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> objects as the content in both the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> and the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>: the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> is set to a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.StackPanel> that contains an <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse> and a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock>; the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> is set to a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.StackPanel> that contains a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock> and a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Label>.
trans-unit.target: A primeira <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem>tem <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>objetos como o conteúdo em ambos o <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A>e o <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>: que <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A>é definido para um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.StackPanel>que contém um <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse>e a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock>o que <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>é definido para um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.StackPanel>que contém um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock>e <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Label>.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Label> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.StackPanel> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock> </xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.StackPanel> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> </xref:System.Windows.UIElement> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A> of the second <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem> is set to a string and the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> is set to a single <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A>Segunda <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem>é definido como uma cadeia de caracteres e o que <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>é definido para um único <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock>.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.TabItem> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.HeaderedContentControl.Header%2A>

trans-unit.source: ![TabControl](~/add/media/controlcontentmodelteabitem.PNG "TabControl") TabControl with different types in the Header property A HeaderedContentControl has a limited default style.
trans-unit.target: ![TabControl](~/add/media/controlcontentmodelteabitem.PNG "TabControl") TabControl com tipos diferentes na propriedade do cabeçalho A HeaderedContentControl tem um estilo padrão limitado.

trans-unit.source: An application developer can create a HeaderedContentControl, but its appearance will be very simple.
trans-unit.target: Um desenvolvedor de aplicativos pode criar um HeaderedContentControl, mas sua aparência será muito simple.

trans-unit.source: If you wish to enhance the appearance of the control, you can create a new <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate>.
trans-unit.target: Se você deseja aprimorar a aparência do controle, você pode criar um novo <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate>.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate>

trans-unit.source: A HeaderedContentControl is useful for creating custom controls because it provides a model for single content controls with headers.
trans-unit.target: Um HeaderedContentControl é útil para a criação de controles personalizados porque ele fornece um modelo para controles de conteúdo único com cabeçalhos.

trans-unit.source: Dependency properties for this control might be set by the control’s default style.
trans-unit.target: Propriedades de dependência para este controle podem ser definidas pelo estilo padrão do controle.

trans-unit.source: If a property is set by a default style, the property might change from its default value when the control appears in the application.
trans-unit.target: Se uma propriedade é definida por um estilo padrão, a propriedade pode ser alterada de seu valor padrão quando o controle é exibido no aplicativo.

trans-unit.source: The default style is determined by which desktop theme is used when the application is running.
trans-unit.target: O estilo padrão é determinado pelo qual tema de área de trabalho é usado quando o aplicativo está em execução.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Default WPF Themes](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=158252).
trans-unit.target: Para obter mais informações, consulte [padrão WPF temas](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=158252).
